The paper applies social network analysis methods to study the dynamics of a popular open source community, Ubuntu, through its IRC channel. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), system dynamics (cs.SD), social and information networks (cs.SOC), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
